ce\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|September 1, 2010\n| \n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2012 National Convention\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Buffalo, New York]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|August 26\u201327, 2012\n|Keynote speech by Richard Lipsitz, Executive Director of Western New York Labor Federation.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2014 Convention\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|October 23\u201324, 2014\n|\n|}\n\n== Prominent members ==\n* [[Robert J. Alexander]]\n* [[Paul Feldman]]\n* [[Sandra Feldman]]\n* [[Carl Gershman]]\n* [[Albert Glotzer]]\n* [[Norman Hill]]\n* [[Sidney Hook]]\n* [[Tom Kahn]]\n* [[Penn Kemble]]\n* [[A. Philip Randolph]]\n* [[Bayard Rustin]]\n* [[August Tyler]]\n* [[Charles S. Zimmerman]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n* {{cite journal|title=The holy alliance: Ronald Reagan and John Paul II<!-- on-line abbreviated title -->; How Reagan and the Pope conspired to assist Poland's Solidarity movement and hasten the demise of Communism <!-- printed, according to citations --> (Cover story)|url=http://www.carlbernstein.com/magazine_holy_alliance.php|journal=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |edition=U.S. |date=February 24, 1992 |first=Carl|last=Bernstein|authorlink=Carl Bernstein|pages=28\u201335|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Bloodworth|first=Jeffrey|title=Losing the center: The decline of American liberalism, 1968\u20131992|year=2013|publisher=The University Press of Kentucky|location=Lexington, Kentucky|isbn=978-0813142296|ref=harv|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IVgyIh320sUC}}\n* {{cite book|title=Supporting the revolution: America, democracy, and the end of the Cold War in Poland, 1981\u20131989|first=Gregory&nbsp;F.|last=Domber<!-- http://www.unf.edu/coas/history/Faculty.aspx -->|publisher=[[ProQuest]]|year=2008|isbn=978-0-549-38516-5|id=[http://www.gwu.edu/~history/graduate_programs/Achievements.cfm Winner of the \"2009 Betty M. Unterberger Prize for Best Dissertation on United States Foreign Policy from the Society for Historians of American Foreign Relations\"]|pages=1\u2013506|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Grtub61ScTgC|type=Ph.D. dissertation (12 September 2007), [[George&nbsp;Washington University]]|ref=harv}} Revised and incorporated in {{cite book|title=Empowering Revolution: America, Poland, and the End of the Cold War|series=The New Cold War History|first=Gregory F.|last=Domber|publisher=University of North Carolina Press books|year=2014|isbn=9781469618517|ref=harv|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Hlk7BAAAQBAJ&q=Gershman%20OR%20Kemble%20OR%20Kahn%20OR%20Horowitz%20OR%20Chenoweth}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Gershman|first=Carl|authorlink=Carl Gershman|title=Totalitarian menace (Controversies: Detente and the left after Afghanistan)|journal=Society|date=3 November 1980|issn=0147-2011|pages=9\u201315|volume=18|issue=1|doi=10.1007/BF02694835|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Harrington|first=Michael|authorlink=Michael Harrington|title=Nuclear threat (Controversies: Detente and the left after Afghanistan)|journal=Society|date=3 November 1980|issn=0147-2011|pages=16\u201321|volume=18|issue=1|doi=10.1007/BF02694836|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|title=Tom Kahn and the Fight for Democracy: A Political Portrait and Personal Recollection|first=Rachelle|last=Horowitz|url=http://www.dissentmagazine.org/wp-content/files_mf/1389822103d11Horowitz.pdf<!-- http://www.socialdemocratsusa.org/oldsite/Kahn.html -->|ref=harv|journal=Democratiya (merged with Dissent in 2009)|issue=Winter|volume=11<!--|issue=Summer|year=2005 last citation is to 2005 publications -->|year=2007|pages=204\u2013251}}\n* {{cite journal|title=How to support ''Solidarnosc'': A debate ('Sponsored by the Committee for the Free World and the League for Industrial Democracy, with introduction by Midge Decter and moderation by Carl Gershman, and held at the Polish Institute for Arts and Sciences, New York City in March 1981')|last1=Kahn|