ight&nbsp;1973|date=December 1972|ref=harv}}<small> \"The following program was adopted at the Social Democrats,&nbsp;U.S.A. and Young People's Socialist League conventions at the end of December, 1972\".</small>\n* {{citation|first=Sidney|last=Hook|authorlink=Sidney Hook|url=http://dissentmagazine.org/democratiya/docs/d3Whole.pdf|id=[https://archive.org/details/TheSocialDemocraticProspect Alternative source]|title=The social&nbsp;democratic prospect|others=originally entitled \"The social &nbsp;democratic prospect: Social democracy and America\"|origyear=17\u201318 July 1976|year=2005|pages=63\u201376|journal=Democratiya, archived by Dissent|ref=harv|issue=Winter|volume=3}}.\n* {{cite book|title=Capitalism, socialism, and democracy|first1=Sidney|last1=Hook|authorlink1=Sidney Hook|first2=Bayard|last2=Rustin|authorlink2=Bayard Rustin|first3=Carl|last3=Gershman|authorlink3=Carl Gershman|first4=Penn|last4=Kemble|authorlink4=Penn Kemble|url=https://archive.org/details/CapitalismSocialismAndDemocracy |location=New York|publisher=Social Democrats, USA|year=1978|series=SD Papers|volume=1|ref=harv|id=Reprinted from ''[[Commentary (magazine)|Commentary]]'' (April 1978) pp.&nbsp;29\u201371}}\n* [[Bayard Rustin]] and Carl Gershman, [https://archive.org/details/AfricaSovietImperialismAndTheRetreatOfAmericanPower ''Africa, Soviet imperialism and the retreat of American power.''] New York: Social Democrats, USA, 1978. <small>(SD papers #2).</small>\n* {{cite journal|first=Carl|last=Gershman|url=https://archive.org/details/AfterTheDominoesFell|title=After the dominoes fell|date=May 1978|series=SD papers|volume=3|journal=Commentary|ref=harv|authorlink=Carl Gershman}}\n* Carl Gershman [https://archive.org/details/TheWorldAccordiingToAndrewYoung ''The world according to Andrew Young.''] New York: Social Democrats, USA, 1978. <small>(SD papers #4).</small>\n* [[Leszek Ko\u0142akowski]] and Sidney Hook, [https://archive.org/details/TheSocialDemocraticChallengeAResponseToConservatism ''